.TH SPM\-REPO\-GEN\-KEY 8 "June 2026" "spm 0.1.0" "System Manager's Manual"
.SH NAME
spm\-repo\-gen\-key \- Generate an Ed25519 signing keypair for a repository
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B spm repo gen-key
\fIname\fR
.SH DESCRIPTION
Generate a new Ed25519 cryptographic keypair for signing repository
Release files.  The keypair is stored as PEM-encoded files under
\fB~/.config/spm/repos/signing\-keys/\fR (or \fB/etc/spm/repos.d/signing\-keys/\fR
for system-wide configuration).
.P
The generated public key fingerprint is displayed after creation.
The repository's configuration in \fB/etc/spm/repos.d/\fR is updated
automatically to reference the new signing key.
.P
Only one keypair per repository is supported.  Running \fBgen-key\fR
on a repository that already has a signing key will overwrite the
existing keypair.
.SH ARGUMENTS
.TP
\fIname\fR
The name of the repository (as configured in \fB/etc/spm/repos.d/\fR).
.SH FILES
.TP
\fB~/.config/spm/repos/signing-keys/<name>.pem\fR
Private key (PEM-encoded Ed25519).
.TP
\fB~/.config/spm/repos/signing-keys/<name>.pub\fR
Public key (PEM-encoded Ed25519).
.SH EXAMPLES
.IP \(bu 2
\fBspm repo gen-key myrepo\fR
Generate a signing keypair for the \fImyrepo\fR repository.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR spm (8),
.BR spm\-repo\-sign (8),
.BR spm\-repo\-publish (8)
.SH AUTHOR
Samad Package Manager <spm@samad.iq>
